## Best Practices

### When to Use What

**Use Turbo Drive for:**
- Standard page navigation
- Form submissions
- Default behavior (it's automatic!)

**Use Turbo Frames for:**
- Updating specific page sections
- Inline editing
- Pagination without full page reload
- Modal content loading

**Use Turbo Streams for:**
- Real-time updates (create, update, delete)
- Multiple simultaneous page updates
- Broadcasting changes to multiple users

**Use Stimulus for:**
- Client-side interactivity
- UI behaviors (dropdowns, modals, tooltips)
- Form enhancements (validation, autosave)
- Anything requiring JavaScript logic

### Common Patterns

**Inline Editing:**
```erb
<%= turbo_frame_tag dom_id(article, :title) do %>
  <h1><%= article.title %></h1>
  <%= link_to "Edit", edit_article_path(article) %>
<% end %>
```

**Optimistic UI Updates:**
```javascript
// Remove item immediately, undo if request fails
async delete(event) {
  const item = event.target.closest('[data-item]')
  item.remove()
  
  try {
    await fetch(this.urlValue, { method: 'DELETE' })
  } catch (error) {
    // Re-add item if deletion failed
    this.element.appendChild(item)
  }
}
```

**Progressive Enhancement:**
```erb
<!-- Works without JavaScript -->
<%= link_to "Delete", article_path(@article), method: :delete %>

<!-- Enhanced with Turbo Streams when JS available -->
<%= button_to "Delete", article_path(@article),
    method: :delete,
    form: { data: { turbo_confirm: "Are you sure?" } } %>
```

